PNIN. In case you decide not to publish it, could you please keep the MS until I return East.

I want to ask you to allow me a little more time for pondering the butterfly book.1 Your conditions suit me; but before definitely committing myself I would like to evolve a precise plan for the book and can only do so after Lermontov is out of the way. When I get back to Cornell, where my papers are, I shall show you some of my own drawings illustrating my theories regarding wing patterns in butterfli